         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... instant(ly) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>107f</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>199</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... in the evenings (?) [and] in the mornings (?) he attached himself to his wife ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... abends [und] morgens (?) hängt er sich an eine Frau.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">... in the evenings [and] in the mornings(?) he attaches himself to a woman.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>107-8</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... or however bones ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... destroy ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... not the tongue ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the mother's own tongue ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>234</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (he went) from the (house) to the Buddha. [11d] He took control of ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (s)he was not [re]born in hell, in this life ...</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="philcomment" subtype="General_remarks">A six-line fragment, with strophe number 11. Recto and verso side as well as metre cannot be determined with certainty.</note><note type="remarks">Fragment of the left side of a leaf, composed of two smaller pieces, badly damaged. On the edge of the verso side traces of a leaf number are still visible.</note><note corresp="#a5" type="philcomment" subtype="General_remarks">There is a typo in <bibl><title corresp="ref:siegandsiegling1949"/></bibl>: the correct reading is <hi>māntau śa</hi> (not <hi>ṣa</hi>). <hi>(ma)māntau</hi> can be a PPt (as suggested by Sieg/Siegling), but <hi>māntau</hi> may also be a 1.sg. subjunctive.</note><note corresp="#b5" type="philcomment" subtype="Transcription">Emendation according to <bibl><title corresp="ref:siegandsiegling1983"/><citedRange>95 f</citedRange></bibl>n. 5.</note></p>
         </div>
